pl_remarks: The Compensated Heat Pulse (CHP) technique was used in combination with the Calibrated Average Gradient (CAG). Sap flow values are calibrated as indicated in Lopez-Bernal et al. (2015, Irrig. Sci.), so azimuthal and radial variabilities as well as other methodological errors should be minimised
